# AGENTS.md — Memstem-aware Codex

Drop this at `~/.codex/AGENTS.md` (or merge into your existing one) so
every Codex session starts with the Memstem-first retrieval rule.
Codex loads this file globally; project-level `AGENTS.md` files
override it for cwd-specific instructions.

## Memory Search Priority — Memstem First, Always

**Memstem is the unified memory index across all your AI agents
(Claude Code, Codex, OpenClaw, anything that drops files on disk).
A grep on this one workspace cannot see cross-agent context.** Use
this ladder for any retrieval-style question — past decisions,
project status, prior work, "do we have a skill for X", "what did
Claude Code do yesterday".

### 1. PRIMARY — Memstem MCP tools

If the `memstem` MCP server is configured in `~/.codex/config.toml`
(see `clients/codex/config.toml.fragment` in the Memstem repo), call
its tools directly:

- `memstem_search` — hybrid lexical + semantic search
- `memstem_get` — fetch a specific memory
- `memstem_list_skills` / `memstem_get_skill`
- `memstem_upsert` — write a new memory (rare; the capture pipeline
  ingests Codex session JSONLs automatically, so deliberate writes
  are usually only for synthesized insights)

### 2. SECONDARY — `memstem` CLI

If the MCP server is not reachable:

```bash
memstem search "your query"
memstem get <id-or-path>
```

### 3. FALLBACK — direct file reads + grep

Only when 1 and 2 are both unavailable, or when you already know the
exact file or string.

### Do NOT default to

- `~/.codex/memories/` — Codex's built-in memory dir. Memstem is the
  single source of truth; do not write here as a primary action.
  Memstem will ingest anything that's already there, but new
  knowledge should land in Memstem via `memstem_upsert` or be left
  in session transcripts for the adapter to pick up.

## Why this matters

Codex sessions write to `~/.codex/sessions/YYYY/MM/DD/rollout-*.jsonl`
on whatever host Codex is running on. The Memstem daemon on that
host watches those files and ingests each session into the unified
index — no Codex cooperation required.

When you search Memstem from Codex, you get back results from every
agent on every host you've connected to the same vault: Codex
sessions from your laptop, Claude Code sessions from your dev server,
OpenClaw notes from Ari, and your own authored memories and skills.
